Garanti Bank, Petkim, Turkcell: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-05-05T06:20:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/garanti-bank-petkim-turkcell-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active in
 Turkey . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the last
close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 634.48, or
0.9 percent, to 69,437.55 yesterday.  Petkim Petrokimya Holding AS (PETKM)  : Turkey’s biggest
petrochemicals producer’s first-quarter net income more than
tripled from a year earlier to 77.2 million liras ($50 million),
it said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the
market closed yesterday. The company was expected to earn 45.3
million liras, according to the average of three analyst
estimates compiled by Bloomberg. Petkim declined 2 kurus, or 0.7
percent, to 2.68 liras.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI): Turkey’s
biggest mobile-phone operator said Avea Iletisim Hizmetleri AS
raised its request for compensation to 47 million liras from 1
million liras in a case it filed in November 2010 against
Turkcell’s tariffs in June-July 2009. Avea, the mobile-phone
operator owned by  Turk Telekomunikasyon AS (TTKOM) , also filed a similar
case against Turkcell, seeking 40 million liras in compensation
for the November 2009-January 2010 period, Turkcell said in a
statement to the bourse after the market closed yesterday.
Turkcell dropped 8 kurus, or 0.9 percent, to 8.94 liras.  Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN)  : Turkey’s biggest
listed bank by market value is expected to report a first-
quarter profit of 739.8 million liras today, according to the
average of seven analyst estimates compiled by Bloomberg. The
bank in which Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA bought a 24.9
percent stake in March, had a net income of 1 billion liras in
the first quarter of 2010. Garanti fell 16 kurus, or 2 percent,
to 8.02 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
